{
  "stem": "10588.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And she-- and Bontsha was suffering.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But he never complained.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "He was always silent.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And that's why the [INAUDIBLE] called him Bontsha the silent.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And he-- not even to his father would he complain.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And one time-- I'm just going to make it brief because it's-- the-- in the coldest winter night, in a drunken stupor, his father threw him out in the cold night, dragged him by the head, and threw him out.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE] And he was-- and he was-- he got himself up, and he went off wherever his eyes took him.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And he was traveling, and then he came in in a big city.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And when he came in there, he was looking for a job, and he became a porter, and again, was abused constantly.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Again, he was silent.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Then-- I'm going, like, quickly through it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Then a woman who had a child that was not his child, an infant, that he married.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And he took the infant when she ran off.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "She left him alone.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And when the infant became 15 years old, he threw out his-- the man who raised him and abused him again.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And on and on, till finally one day, he was run over by a horse and carriage.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And he, whatever happened, he never complained, never raised his voice-- not to God, not to man.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "His suffering was more terrible than Job's, but never complained.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "That's-- and then finally, even in the hospital, when he lie in the hospital, he, where everybody is allowed to scream and he wasn't treated well because had not enough money to pay.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And in silence, he lived.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "In silence, he died.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And when they buried him, and they put the piece of wood, a woman, the gravedigger's wife, the wind blew away the piece of wood.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And nobody knew where he was, who was laying where.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "That this was Bontsha.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And she used it to cook her potatoes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And in the book, the story said that if he had a name, even if the 100 years, maybe somebody would say that 'Here lays Bontsha.' In this way, he vanished, like he would never live, even like a grain of sand.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And then, when he came to the next world, he was-- everybody knew-- they treated him well.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And they said, 'In the other world where you came from, there is no justice.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "But in this world is justice.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And anything you want is yours.'",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he couldn't believe.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Why would somebody be so nice here if nobody was nice there?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he said, '[NON-ENGLISH]?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Really?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Really?' In Yiddish, [NON-ENGLISH] is 'really.' And he said, 'Yes.' So after giving it a lot of thought, he said, 'Well, in that case, what I would wish, your excellency, is every morning for breakfast a hot roll with butter.'",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And when I was in Auschwitz, I was thinking, the biggest millionaire couldn't have a roll, a hot roll with butter.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "To have some bread, I understood at that time, the story.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I also understood that six million have no graves and no markers, just like Bontsha [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I understood something much deeper than that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "To me, even though my mother didn't say this, because when she-- but I felt-- we would have had a homeland.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We wouldn't be an orphan like Bontsha [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Nobody would keep us chasing from place to place, and even if we lived for so many years.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My family, on my mother's side, came to Poland in the 1600 century from Germany.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And four generations were still alive, you know, when they came in.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And when we left there-- and I never will remember a remark that somebody made.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "A non-Jewish child said to me, 'The houses are yours, but the streets are ours.'",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And after living so many years, and not to be a trace left, that is something.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's why of all the stories, this one had the greatest impact, because I didn't know that one day I will be an orphan and will starved and tortured.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But what I remember, at that time, when I asked my mother, 'How could Bontsha endure so much suffering?'",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my mother, may she rest in peace, answered, in Yiddish, '[YIDDISH]'-- and I'll explain it, what it means in English. '[YIDDISH].",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Sometimes a man is stronger than iron, and other times, weaker than a fly.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But,' she said, 'we never know our strength till we haven't been tested.'",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
